      "writtenOn": "2021-05-10T21:43:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hm, right.\n\nI think that actually in all cases right now we\u0027d like to copy status from the attempt reported from CQDaemon; in this particular case, makeAttempt could still create an attempt with FAILURE, because in this code we don\u0027t know that the run is considered failed because of failed submission, it could be something else. Then in reconcileAttempts, the \"SUCCESS\" status could be copied over from the CQD Attempt.\n\nThen, later on when there\u0027s an easy way to check that the run is considered failed only because of submit failure, then in order to maintain backward-compatibility, we\u0027ll change this to set status \u003d SUCCESS, substatus \u003d FAILED_SUBMIT?",
      "parentUuid": "54b7466d_ef9e133e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 115,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 115,
        "endChar": 39
