      "writtenOn": "2021-05-07T20:21:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "+Yiwei\n\nIn our doc[1] we differentiate between 4 CL submission statuses:\nPENDING (not tried), \nUNKNOWN (tried, but didn\u0027t get result from Gerrit), \nFAILURE (Gerrit refused),\nSUCCESS (submitted)\n\nI\u0027m not 100% sure how valuable `UNKNOWN` is, but I see certain value in distinguishing between Gerrit refusal and never trying to submit.\n\nCan you add data to run.Submission [2] to provide for BQ data generation of at least FAILURE \u003c-\u003e PENDING?\n\n[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/main:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/cv/api/bigquery/v1/attempt.proto;l\u003d109;drc\u003d15d76ce535c523ee816722a2f90b7ea41ac6abcf\n[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/main:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/cv/internal/run/storage.proto;l\u003d91;drc\u003d7d50ff191988822219b4ef8ee33e81e5b701450f",
      "revId": "0ccf940f7fe66781b5f5a135700d282702b5c3b1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
